value.value: A cell population phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of ascospore formation is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype in which ascospore wall biogenesis does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype in which ascospore wall assembly does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype in which ascospore formation begins later than normal.
A cell population phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of ascospore formation is increased.
A cellular process phenotype in which the rate, or speed, of ascospore formation is increased, i.e. sporulation takes place more rapidly than in wild type.
A cellular process phenotype in which ascospore formation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transposition is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transposition does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of transposition is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of transposition is increased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of transposition is increased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transposition is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal vacuolar transport during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vacuolar transport is abnormal.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) to or from the vacuole. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of vacuolar transport is decreased.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) to or from the vacuole. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of vacuolar transport is decreased.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) to or from the vacuole. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vacuolar transport begins later than normal.

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) to or from the vacuole. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vacuolar transport is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This term can be used for protein transport or for the movement of other substances (e.g. lipids or ions) to or from the vacuole. If it is used for a protein transport phenotype, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is abnormal.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of G1 phase of a mitotic cell cycle is shorter than normal.
A cellular process phenotype in which progression through M phase of the mitotic cell cycle is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic M phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in M phase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

definition.value: M phase is often identified by the degree of chromosome condensation. Use this term for terminal arrest. If arrest is transient, consider using 'increased duration of mitotic cell cycle phase' (FYPO:0001069) or one of its more specific descendants.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is abnormally arrested in S phase.

definition.value: Cells arrested in S phase typically have more than 1C, but less than 2C, DNA content. Use this term for terminal arrest. If arrest is transient, consider using 'increased duration of mitotic cell cycle phase' (FYPO:0001069) or one of its more specific descendants.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is longer than normal.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is shorter than normal.
A cellular process phenotype in which progression through mitotic anaphase is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through anaphase of mitosis is longer than normal.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic anaphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in anaphase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in metaphase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

definition.value: Metaphase is defined as the part of mitosis when chromosomes are aligned in the middle of the spindle. If no spindle is present, do not use this term, but consider 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic prophase' (FYPO:0003145). Also do not use this term if the spindle has elongated at all. If the spindle has elongated, or you cannot tell whether a spindle is present, or metaphase cannot be clearly detected, annotate to the more general term 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic M phase' (FYPO:0000608). In cells that arrest in metaphase, chromosome separation does not occur.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the onset of metaphase of mitosis begins later than normal.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic telophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in telophase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.
A transcription regulation phenotype in which any process of positive regulation of transcription is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. There may be enough evidence to support annotation to a more specific term such as 'abnormal transcriptional response to pheromone' (FYPO:0000984); if not, it is safer to annotate to 'increased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000780) or 'decreased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000781) rather than explicitly claiming that an effect on regulation was observed.

label.value: abnormal negative regulation of transcription during vegetative growth

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which any process of negative regulation of transcription is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. There may be enough evidence to support annotation to a more specific term such as 'abnormal chromatin silencing' (FYPO:0000144); if not, it is safer to annotate to 'increased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000780) or 'decreased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000781) rather than explicitly claiming that an effect on regulation was observed.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which premeiotic DNA replication is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal initiation of premeiotic DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the initiation of premeiotic DNA replication is abnormal.
A phenotype in which a specific cellular process is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A phenotype in which a specific cellular process is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which programmed cell death by apoptosis is abnormal. Apoptosis is a form of cell death characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), plasma membrane blebbing and fragmentation of the cell into apoptotic bodies.
A cellular process phenotype in which biofilm formation is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype that affects progression of the mitotic or meiotic cell cycle, or regulation of cell cycle progression.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects mitochondrial translation.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to G418. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of G418 that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abolished protein localization to centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: Auxotrophy in which a cell is unable to synthesize leucine, and therefore requires leucine in the medium for vegetative cell growth.
A cell population phenotype in which a cell population in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle grows at a faster rate than normal.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: increased cell population growth rate on glucose carbon source

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a cell population in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle grows at a faster rate than normal in a medium containing glucose as the carbon source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septum assembly begins later than normal.

label.value: abnormal chromatin silencing at centromere central core

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing is abnormal at the centromere central core. Chromatin silencing is the observed effect of processes that repress transcription at the centromere central core, which is normally assembled into CENP-A-containing chromatin.

definition.value: Note that the centromere central core corresponds to SO:0001796. Chromatin silencing phenotypes at the centromere central core may reflect the assembly or maintenance of CENP-A-containing chromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'CENP-A containing chromatin' (GO:0061638), and the biological process term 'CENP-A containing chromatin organization' (GO:0061641).

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of chromosome organization is abnormal. Chromosome organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of chromosomes.
